Sarge, we got the Deputy
Superintendent of Police

780
00:34:50,942 --> 00:34:52,109
tipping off our target.

781
00:34:52,134 --> 00:34:53,700
- I don't know how to proceed.
- Bury it.

782
00:34:54,344 --> 00:34:55,377
What?

783
00:34:55,412 --> 00:34:57,079
Keep it out of your paper.

784
00:34:57,113 --> 00:34:58,621
It's too hot.

785
00:34:59,549 --> 00:35:02,125
Listen, I'm gonna take
the lead on this, only me.

786
00:35:02,619 --> 00:35:04,420
I'll deal with Brennan.

787
00:35:04,454 --> 00:35:05,754
Sarge.

788
00:35:05,789 --> 00:35:07,556
The Glock we recovered at Deisha's,

789
00:35:07,591 --> 00:35:08,857
it's a match for all of our vics,

790
00:35:08,892 --> 00:35:10,526
Hoffman, DeVante, Kev.

791
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:12,561
I've also got a CI who puts
Griffin hiding

792
00:35:12,596 --> 00:35:13,862
at a flophouse on Monroe.

793
00:35:13,897 --> 00:35:15,137
We got this prick.

794
00:35:15,171 --> 00:35:17,666
All right, start typing a warrant.
I'll get a judge.

795
00:35:17,701 --> 00:35:20,018
We move in hot, fully loaded.

796
00:35:20,870 --> 00:35:23,339
I don't care if he comes out in a bag.

797
00:35:23,373 --> 00:35:25,608
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

798
00:35:25,642 --> 00:35:28,110
<i>♪ </i>

799
00:35:28,144 --> 00:35:30,346
- You ready?
- Yeah.

800
00:35:30,380 --> 00:35:36,552
<i>♪ </i>

801
00:35:36,586 --> 00:35:38,036
Here we go.

802
00:35:39,222 --> 00:35:40,856
Got eyes on Griffin.

803
00:35:42,425 --> 00:35:43,892
All right, standby, he's pulling up.

804
00:35:43,927 --> 00:35:51,200
<i>♪ </i>

805
00:36:05,248 --> 00:36:06,915
He's on the phone.

806
00:36:06,950 --> 00:36:08,951
Wait till he gets out, Antonio.

807
00:36:08,985 --> 00:36:16,225
<i>♪ </i>

808
00:36:17,827 --> 00:36:19,328
Take him.

809
00:36:19,362 --> 00:36:21,263
[TIRES SCREECHING]

810
00:36:21,297 --> 00:36:24,266
<i>[EXCITING MUSIC]</i>

811
00:36:24,300 --> 00:36:25,601
Chicago PD.

812
00:36:25,635 --> 00:36:30,606
<i>♪ </i>

813
00:36:30,640 --> 00:36:32,775
Put your hands against the car.

814
00:36:32,809 --> 00:36:34,309
Put your hands on the car now.

815
00:36:35,612 --> 00:36:37,579
- You got me?
- Yeah.

816
00:36:37,614 --> 00:36:44,653
<i>♪ </i>

817
00:36:48,725 --> 00:36:50,426
Why are you smiling, Andre?

818
00:36:51,394 --> 00:36:53,027
You think you've won.

819
00:36:53,496 --> 00:36:54,988
It's amusing.

820
00:36:55,632 --> 00:36:57,991
They can't protect you anymore.

821
00:36:58,835 --> 00:37:00,636
You don't know nothing, fool.

822
00:37:03,159 --> 00:37:04,789
Let me ask you something.

823
00:37:05,475 --> 00:37:07,409
That funny too?

824
00:37:08,978 --> 00:37:10,879
Where were you when they shot
your cousin?

825
00:37:10,914 --> 00:37:12,171
Answer that.

826
00:37:12,982 --> 00:37:15,818
I'm done talking. My lawyer's on the way.

827
00:37:20,963 --> 00:37:22,764
I hope he's a good one.

828
00:37:28,398 --> 00:37:29,698
[DOOR CLOSES]

829
00:37:36,439 --> 00:37:37,706
Hank.

830
00:37:40,777 --> 00:37:42,778
What can I do for you, Kate?

831
00:37:46,349 --> 00:37:49,318
[SIGHS] I need you to release
Andre Griffin.

832
00:37:50,587 --> 00:37:53,322
- Excuse me?
- I talked to State's attorney's office.

833
00:37:53,356 --> 00:37:55,591
The evidence is weak. There's
no fingerprints on the gun,

834
00:37:55,625 --> 00:37:57,025
there were no witnesses.

835
00:37:57,060 --> 00:38:01,029
The defense is gonna tear
this case to pieces.

836
00:38:01,064 --> 00:38:04,766
Case is strong, so...

837
00:38:05,969 --> 00:38:07,770
If there's nothing else...

838
00:38:07,804 --> 00:38:09,071
We have an agreement, Hank.

839
00:38:12,075 --> 00:38:14,510
We made it after I helped Olinsky.

840
00:38:15,912 --> 00:38:17,279
Don't bring Al into this.

841
00:38:17,313 --> 00:38:18,446
I told you...

842
00:38:20,083 --> 00:38:22,785
I told you there would be
a time when I ask you to

843
00:38:22,819 --> 00:38:27,022
solve cases in a hurry
or not... in a hurry.

844
00:38:27,056 --> 00:38:28,690
This is one of those.

845
00:38:33,383 --> 00:38:35,651
I know it was you who tipped off Griffin.

846
00:38:35,676 --> 00:38:37,381
Excuse me?

847
00:38:37,834 --> 00:38:40,769
His girlfriend saw you talking to him

848
00:38:40,804 --> 00:38:43,105
a couple hours before
he killed his cousin.

849
00:38:45,675 --> 00:38:47,643
And tried to kill my man, Atwater.

850
00:38:47,677 --> 00:38:48,911
I am three generations police,

851
00:38:48,945 --> 00:38:50,746
don't question my loyalty.

852
00:38:50,780 --> 00:38:53,382
You're not loyal to the job.
You're loyal to Kelton.

853
00:38:53,416 --> 00:38:56,526
I am. He's a good man,
and he's a good cop.

854
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:59,488
He is responsible for my career,

855
00:38:59,522 --> 00:39:01,405
I am not going to let him down.

856
00:39:02,525 --> 00:39:04,660
How long has he been in bed
with the gangs?

857
00:39:04,951 --> 00:39:06,154
With Griffin?

858
00:39:06,188 --> 00:39:09,765
He had absolutely no idea
that Griffin was involved.

859
00:39:09,799 --> 00:39:13,669
- Until Bernie got shot.
- Nobody wants this, Hank.

860
00:39:13,703 --> 00:39:16,629
- Nobody.
- When Atwater was in surgery...

861
00:39:17,507 --> 00:39:20,909
I mean, you stood right next
to me, looked me in the eye.

862
00:39:20,944 --> 00:39:24,011
You told me you'd do whatever
you can to help.

863
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:27,082
The whole time you knew it was
Griffin who did the shooting?

864
00:39:27,116 --> 00:39:29,818
All I did was tell him
that he was up for the murder,

865
00:39:29,853 --> 00:39:31,653
that the police were
looking at him, that's it.

866
00:39:31,688 --> 00:39:34,423
I didn't know that he was gonna
shoot Atwater.

867
00:39:34,457 --> 00:39:36,233
You crossed a line.

868
00:39:36,267 --> 00:39:38,994
You wanna lecture me about
crossing a line, Hank?

869
00:39:39,028 --> 00:39:40,629
This is our line of business.

870
00:39:40,663 --> 00:39:42,598
Sometimes we do things
we're not proud of.

871
00:39:42,632 --> 00:39:44,132
You know that better than anyone.

872
00:39:45,535 --> 00:39:47,002
[SIGHS]

873
00:39:48,310 --> 00:39:49,677
What does that mean?

874
00:39:53,209 --> 00:39:54,943
You look the other way.

875
00:39:56,579 --> 00:39:58,480
You release Andre Griffin.

876
00:40:02,886 --> 00:40:04,820
Get the hell out of my office.

877
00:40:04,854 --> 00:40:07,823
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

878
00:40:07,857 --> 00:40:14,930
<i>♪ </i>

879
00:40:18,201 --> 00:40:19,868
Thank you.

880
00:40:21,738 --> 00:40:24,206
Thank you. Thanks for coming.

881
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:26,575
Hey, I heard about Griffin.
I thought you might be here.

882
00:40:26,609 --> 00:40:28,143
- Get out of my way.
- Calm down, let it go.

883
00:40:28,177 --> 00:40:29,464
You gotta let it go, all right?

884
00:40:29,498 --> 00:40:31,430
It might as well have been
them that shot Kevin.

885
00:40:31,464 --> 00:40:33,482
- Kevin's gonna be all right.
- That's not the point.

886
00:40:33,516 --> 00:40:35,166
I know, you think I like this?

887
00:40:35,718 --> 00:40:38,086
Calling them out in public
makes you look bad.

888
00:40:38,121 --> 00:40:40,656
These two are more dangerous
than ten Griffins.

889
00:40:40,690 --> 00:40:43,592
So, we gotta be smart,
and we gotta be patient.

890
00:40:43,626 --> 00:40:44,993
We're playing the long game here.

891
00:40:47,597 --> 00:40:49,498
This is Chicago.

892
00:40:49,532 --> 00:40:52,901
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

893
00:40:52,936 --> 00:41:00,008
<i>♪ </i>

